The paper deals with information retrieval and storage, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses security and privacy constraints, which are relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a new achievable scheme based on a special structure, which could be of interest to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
